-- China Stocks: Citic Securities, Baoshan Steel, Sinohydro
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-01-17T08:21:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/china-stocks-citic-securities-baoshan-steel-sinohydro.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses as of the close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index (SHCOMP) , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, jumped 92.18 points, or 4.2 percent, to
2,298.38, its biggest gain since Oct. 9, 2009. The  CSI 300 Index 
gained 4.9 percent to 2,460.60.  Brokerages:  Citic Securities Co. (600030)  (600030 CH), China’s
biggest listed brokerage, surged 6.9 percent to 10.51 yuan.
Haitong Securities Co. (600837 CH) jumped 6.7 percent to 8.15
yuan.  China’s  National Social Security Fund  has won approval to
invest 100 billion yuan ($15.8 billion) from local pensions in
stocks and bonds, the China Securities Journal reported today.
Almost 30 to 40 percent of the new funds provided by an
unidentified southern province will probably be invested in
stocks, the newspaper reported, without saying where it got the
information.  Baoshan Iron & Steel Co.  (600019 CH), the listed unit of
China’s second-biggest steelmaker, gained 2.4 percent to 5.19
yuan. Its parent bought 175 million shares in the company,
increasing its stake to 74.97 percent from 73.97 percent,
Baoshan Steel said in a statement.  Sinohydro Group Ltd. (601669)  (601669 CH), the nation’s biggest
builder of dams, jumped 6.4 percent to 4.18 yuan, its biggest
gain since Oct. 18. Sinohydro won 127.8 billion yuan in new
contracts in 2011, the company said in a statement.  --Zhang Shidong. Editor: Richard Frost  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
